'''疫苗猶豫'''是指儘管可以接種[[疫苗|疫苗]]，但仍延遲或拒絕接受疫苗。疫苗猶豫原因複雜，可隨時間、地點、疫苗的不同而有所差異<ref>{{Cite web |last=SAGE |first=Working Group |date=1 October 2014 |title=Report of the SAGE working group on vaccine hesitancy |url=https://www.who.int/immunization/sage/meetings/2014/october/1_Report_WORKING_GROUP_vaccine_hesitancy_final.pdf |url-status=no |website=WHO |access-date=2021-07-13 |archive-date=2021-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025133401/https://www.who.int/immunization/sage/meetings/2014/october/1_Report_WORKING_GROUP_vaccine_hesitancy_final.pdf }}</ref>，受到自滿、便利性、{{le|風險感知|Risk perception|風險感知能力}}、患者長壽於接種者等因素的影響<ref name="Smith2015" />。疫苗猶豫包括完全拒絕接種疫苗、推遲接種疫苗、接種了疫苗但不信任而要強制他人、或僅使用某些疫苗但不使用其他疫苗<ref name="Smith2015">{{Cite journal |last=Smith |first=MJ |date=November 2015 |title=Promoting Vaccine Confidence |journal=Infectious Disease Clinics of North America |type=Review |volume=29 |issue=4 |pages=759–69 |doi=10.1016/j.idc.2015.07.004 |pmid=26337737}}</ref><ref name="Larson2014">{{Cite journal |last1=Larson |first1=HJ |last2=Jarrett |first2=C |last3=Eckersberger |first3=E |last4=Smith |first4=DM |last5=Paterson |first5=P |date=April 2014 |title=Understanding vaccine hesitancy around vaccines and vaccination from a global perspective: a systematic review of published literature, 2007–2012. |journal=Vaccine |volume=32 |issue=19 |pages=2150–59 |doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2014.01.081 |pmid=24598724}}</ref>。若是完全反對疫苗，會被稱為'''反疫苗人士'''（anti-vaxxer；這種思想叫做anti-vaccinationism或anti-vax beliefs）<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hinsliff |first=Gaby |date=16 November 2020 |title=It's the 'vaccine hesitant', not anti-vaxxers, who are troubling public health experts |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/nov/16/vaccine-hesitant-anti-vaxxers-public-health-experts-covid |access-date=2021-09-28 |archive-date=2021-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210904150653/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/nov/16/vaccine-hesitant-anti-vaxxers-public-health-experts-covid |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

科學界[[科學共識|廣泛認為]]疫苗安全並且有效<ref>{{Cite journal |date=October 2017 |title=Communicating science-based messages on vaccines |journal=Bulletin of the World Health Organization |volume=95 |issue=10 |pages=670–71 |doi=10.2471/BLT.17.021017 |pmc=5689193 |pmid=29147039}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.vox.com/2018/8/21/17588104/vaccine-opposition-anti-vaxxer |title=Why do some people oppose vaccination? |work=Vox |access-date=2018-11-26 |archive-date=2019-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190921013342/https://www.vox.com/2018/8/21/17588104/vaccine-opposition-anti-vaxxer |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://theconversation.com/defending-science-how-the-art-of-rhetoric-can-help-68210 |title=Defending science: How the art of rhetoric can help |last=Ceccarelli |first=Leah |work=The Conversation |access-date=2018-11-26 |language=en |archive-date=2019-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105052610/https://theconversation.com/defending-science-how-the-art-of-rhetoric-can-help-68210 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vaccines.gov/basics/safety/index.html |title=Vaccines.gov |last=U.S. Department of Health and Human Services |website=Vaccines.gov |language=en-us |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-date=2019-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190313190815/https://www.vaccines.gov/basics/safety/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。疫苗猶豫往往導致[[疾病爆發|疾病爆發]]並造成{{le|疫苗可預防的疾病|Vaccine-preventable diseases|疫苗原可避免}}的死亡<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.childrenshospital.org/centers-and-services/division-of-infectious-diseases/faq-resurgence-of-measles |title=Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) |website=Boston Children's Hospital |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017113035/http://www.childrenshospital.org/centers-and-services/division-of-infectious-diseases/faq-resurgence-of-measles |archive-date=October 17, 2013 |access-date=February 11, 2014}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{Cite journal |vauthors=Phadke VK, Bednarczyk RA, Salmon DA, Omer SB |date=March 2016 |title=Association Between Vaccine Refusal and Vaccine Preventable Diseases in the United States: A Review of Measles and Pertussis |journal=JAMA |volume=315 |issue=11 |pages=1149–58 |doi=10.1001/jama.2016.1353 |pmc=5007135 |pmid=26978210}}</ref><ref name="wolfesharp">{{Cite journal|title=Anti-vaccinationists past and present|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1123944/|last=Wolfe|first=Robert M|last2=Sharp|first2=Lisa K|date=2002-08-24|journal=BMJ : British Medical Journal|issue=7361|doi=10.1136/bmj.325.7361.430|volume=325|pages=430–432|issn=0959-8138|pmc=1123944|pmid=12193361|access-date=2019-03-14|archive-date=2021-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313093125/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1123944/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="AgeOld">{{Cite journal |vauthors=Poland GA, Jacobson RM |date=January 2011 |title=The age-old struggle against the antivaccinationists |url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/ef30916a843202d73362f06b38ed5084e31eb8aa |journal=The New England Journal of Medicine |volume=364 |issue=2 |pages=97–99 |doi=10.1056/NEJMp1010594 |pmid=21226573 |s2cid=39229852 |access-date=2021-07-15 |archive-date=2021-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305194504/https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/The-age-old-struggle-against-the-Poland-Jacobson/ef30916a843202d73362f06b38ed5084e31eb8aa |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.wired.com/magazine/2009/10/ff_waronscience/all/1 |title=An epidemic of fear: how panicked parents skipping shots endangers us all |last=Wallace A |date=2009-10-19 |work=Wired |access-date=2009-10-21 |archive-date=2013-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131225110404/http://www.wired.com/magazine/2009/10/ff_waronscience/all/1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Poland GA, Jacobson RM |date=March 2001 |title=Understanding those who do not understand: a brief review of the anti-vaccine movement |journal=Vaccine |volume=19 |issue=17–19 |pages=2440–45 |doi=10.1016/S0264-410X(00)00469-2 |pmid=11257375}}</ref>。因此，[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]將疫苗猶豫列為2019年十大全球衞生威脅之一<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019年全球卫生面临的10项威胁|url=https://www.who.int/zh/emergencies/ten-threats-to-global-health-in-2019|work=世界衞生組織|accessdate=2019-03-14|language=zh|author=|date=2019|publisher=世界衞生組織|archive-date=2019-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020133524/https://www.who.int/zh/emergencies/ten-threats-to-global-health-in-2019|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.who.int/emergencies/ten-threats-to-global-health-in-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190627025209/http://www.who.int/emergencies/ten-threats-to-global-health-in-2019 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2019-06-27 |title=Ten threats to global health in 2019 |website=Who.int |language=en |access-date=2020-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.newsweek.com/world-health-organization-who-un-global-health-air-pollution-anti-vaxxers-1292493 |title=The anti-vax movement has been listed by WHO as one of its top 10 health threats for 2019 |last=PM |first=Aristos Georgiou |date=2019-01-15 |access-date=2019-01-16 |language=en |archive-date=2019-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122050616/https://www.newsweek.com/world-health-organization-who-un-global-health-air-pollution-anti-vaxxers-1292493 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。然而需要注意的是，「疫苗」為多種不同種類疫苗的統稱，僅管多數疫苗能帶來的利益遠大於接種風險，但這並不保障任何種類的疫苗或某種疫苗中的所有批號皆為安全無慮。

疫苗猶豫主要起因於疫苗相關的醫學、倫理、法律議題的爭議，涉及多個關鍵因素，包括對疫苗和/或[[醫療衛生提供者|醫療衛生提供者]]沒有信心、自滿（未能發覺疫苗的需求性或疫苗的價值）和便利性問題（不易取得疫苗施打）<ref name="Larson2014" />。有關疫苗的爭議自發明疫苗接種以來就存在，比“疫苗”（{{lang|en|vaccine}}）和“疫苗接種”（{{lang|en|vaccination}}）這兩個術語早將近八十年出現。有報告顯示反疫苗人士提出的假說也會隨著時間改變<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Gerber JS, Offit PA |date=February 2009 |title=Vaccines and autism: a tale of shifting hypotheses |journal=Clinical Infectious Diseases |volume=48 |issue=4 |pages=456–61 |doi=10.1086/596476 |pmc=2908388 |pmid=19128068}}</ref> 。

擬議要求接種疫苗的法案，例如{{le|加州參議院第277號法案|California Senate Bill 277}}和澳大利亞的{{le|No Jab No Pay|No Jab, No Pay}}政策，遭{{le|反疫苗組織|List of anti-vaccination groups}}的反對<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://discovermagazine.com/2018/dec/fostering-fear |title=The Long History of America's Anti-Vaccination Movement |access-date=2019-02-02 |website=DiscoverMagazine.com |archive-date=2019-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022194720/http://discovermagazine.com/2018/dec/fostering-fear |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/how-anti-vax-went-viral/ |title=How anti-vax went viral |last=Young |first=Zachary |date=2018-11-21 |access-date=2019-02-02 |archive-date=2020-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815004945/https://www.politico.eu/article/how-anti-vax-went-viral/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/anti-vaxxers-italy-vaccine-measles-epidemic-europe-us-vaccination-global-health-security-agenda-a8560021.html |title=How the anti-vaxxers are winning in Italy |date=2018-09-28 |access-date=2019-02-02 |language=en |archive-date=2020-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702112028/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/anti-vaxxers-italy-vaccine-measles-epidemic-europe-us-vaccination-global-health-security-agenda-a8560021.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。反對{{le|疫苗接種政策|Vaccination policy}}的觀點可包括擔心會侵犯[[公民自由|公民自由]]或降低公眾對疫苗接種的信任、或懷疑製藥業藉此牟取暴利<ref name="wolfesharp" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mystatesman.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/civil-liberties-center-vaccination-debate-texas/lWzq91qhSyAKcY8MiaWnYM/ |title='Civil liberties' at center of vaccination debate in Texas |last=Chang |first=Julie |date=12 July 2017 |website=Mystatesman |publisher=Austin American-Statesman |access-date=2021-07-20 |archive-date=2017-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713075809/https://www.mystatesman.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/civil-liberties-center-vaccination-debate-texas/lWzq91qhSyAKcY8MiaWnYM/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2014/03/23/making-vaccination-mandatory-for-all-children/in-britain-vaccinate-with-persuasion-not-coercion |title=In Britain, Vaccinate With Persuasion, not Coercion |last1=Elliman |first1=David |last2=Bedford |first2=Helen |date=23 March 2014 |website=The New York Times |access-date=2021-07-20 |archive-date=2014-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140324030057/https://www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2014/03/23/making-vaccination-mandatory-for-all-children/in-britain-vaccinate-with-persuasion-not-coercion |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://health.spectator.co.uk/anti-vaxxers-have-embraced-social-media-were-paying-for-fake-news-with-real-lives/ |title=Anti-vaxxers have embraced social media. We're paying for fake news with real lives |date=2017-06-28 |access-date=2019-02-02 |language=en-GB |archive-date=2019-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405124330/https://health.spectator.co.uk/anti-vaxxers-have-embraced-social-media-were-paying-for-fake-news-with-real-lives/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>Bourree Lam, [https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2015/02/vaccines-are-profitable-so-what/385214/ Vaccines Are Profitable, So What?] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2015/02/vaccines-are-profitable-so-what/385214/ |date=20200812190526 }}. ''The Atlantic'' Feb. 10, 2015</ref>。

==疫苗的效用 ==
[[File:Rubella_in_the_US_1966-2017.png|thumb]]感染情形普遍減少，資料來自[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国疾病控制与预防中心]]]]

大量科學證據顯示，大規模的疫苗注射活動是有效的<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Effects of a large-scale intervention with influenza and 23-valent pneumococcal vaccines in adults aged 65 years or older: a prospective study|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11293594/|last=Christenson|first=B.|last2=Lundbergh|first2=P.|date=2001-03-31|journal=Lancet (London, England)|issue=9261|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(00)04237-9|volume=357|pages=1008–1011|issn=0140-6736|pmid=11293594|last3=Hedlund|first3=J.|last4=Ortqvist|first4=A.|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211123043125/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11293594/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。疫苗接種計劃曾幫助消除[[天花|天花]]<ref name="Fenner">{{cite book|author=Fenner F, Henderson DA, Arita I, Ježek Z, Ladnyi, ID|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/smallpox/9241561106.pdf|accessdate=2007-09-04|format=PDF|title=Smallpox and its Eradication|publisher=World Health Organization|location=Geneva|year=1988|isbn=92-4-156110-6|archive-date=2007-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927092931/http://whqlibdoc.who.int/smallpox/9241561106.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，脊髓灰質炎也幾乎因疫苗接種計劃而遭{{le|根除脊髓灰質炎|poliomyelitis eradication|根除}}<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Mass vaccination campaigns for polio eradication: an essential strategy for success|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16989271/|last=Sutter|first=R. W.|last2=Maher|first2=C.|date=2006|journal=Current Topics in Microbiology and Immunology|doi=10.1007/3-540-36583-4_11|volume=304|pages=195–220|issn=0070-217X|pmid=16989271|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211122132047/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16989271/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此外，自1988年美國開始注射[[流感嗜血桿菌|流感嗜血桿菌]]的疫苗後，因流感嗜血桿菌導致的疾病（如[[細菌性腦膜炎|細菌性腦膜炎]]及其他兒童重症）的感染人數下降超過99%<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Progress toward elimination of Haemophilus influenzae type b invasive disease among infants and children--United States, 1998-2000|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11925021/|last=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)|date=2002-03-22|journal=MMWR. Morbidity and mortality weekly report|issue=11|volume=51|pages=234–237|issn=0149-2195|pmid=11925021|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211123041807/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11925021/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。若某一年在美國出生的兒童，從出生到成年過程都接受完整的疫苗注射，估計可以減少三萬三千人死亡，也可以避免一千四百萬個感染病例<ref>{{cite news|author=Park A|url=http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1808438-1,00.html|title=How safe are vaccines?|work=Time|date=2008-05-21|accessdate=2016-09-21|archive-date=2013-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525205209/http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1808438-1,00.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

某些疫苗反對者認為，感染人數下降不是因為疫苗，而是因為環境衛生和個人衛生得到改善，或者是在導入疫苗前，病症的罹患人數就已經在下降。此說法沒有科學數據支持。在疫苗出現前，疫苗可預防疾病的發生率多半會隨時間而起伏，在疫苗出現後發生率幾乎降到零。[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国疾病控制与预防中心]]網站有一篇文章是要打擊對於疫苗的誤解，其中提到「我們要相信每個疾病都在相關疫苗導入時，恰好因為衛生改善而造成感染人數快速下降嗎？」<ref name="CDC: common misconceptions">{{cite web|title=Some common misconceptions about vaccination and how to respond to them|url=http://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/vac-gen/6mishome.htm|accessdate=2012-09-28|publisher=<nowiki>National Center for Immunization and Respiratory Diseases]], Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</nowiki>|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150120055820/http://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/vac-gen/6mishome.htm|archivedate=2015-01-20|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。

反疫苗運動另外呼籲的一件事是用隨機[[臨床試驗|臨床試驗]]來證明疫苗性有效性，其中[[實驗組|實驗組]]的兒童接受疫苗注射，而受控組的兒童則不進行注射。此一實驗會刻意的讓一些兒童拒絕標準的醫療，違反研究倫理學，因此實驗不可能通過。目前有一些針對有注射疫苗和未注射疫苗的比較研究，但不是隨機性的研究。而且，已有文獻證實疫苗的安全性較其他實驗中的方式要好<ref>{{cite book |last1=Novella |first1=Steven |first2=Bob |last2=Novella |first3=Cara |last3=Santa Maria |first4=Jay |last4=Novella |first5=Evan |last5=Bernstein |title=The Skeptics' Guide to the Universe: How to Know What's Really Real in a World Increasingly Full of Fake |publisher=Grand Central Publishing |date=2018 |page=185 |isbn=9781538760512}}</ref>。

有些批評者認為因為疫苗而產生的免疫是暫時的，需要追加疫苗接種，而罹患疾病後仍存活的人會有永久的免疫力<ref name="wolfesharp" />。如以下討論的，替代醫學的理念和疫苗有效的概念是無法並容的<ref name="Ernst" />

=== 公共衛生 ===
[[File:Charlotte_Cleverley-Bisman.jpg|thumb]]來保護她，避免兒童在很小還無法接種疫苗時就感這類疾病<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wane|first1=Joanna|title=The case for vaccination|url=http://www.biocsl.co.nz/docs/957/642/NorthSouth_case-for-accination.pdf|website=North & South|accessdate=2015-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150824083950/http://www.biocsl.co.nz/docs/957/642/NorthSouth_case-for-accination.pdf|archive-date=2015-08-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>]]
不完整的疫苗接種會增加整個群體的風險，也包括那些已接種疫苗的人，因為不完整的疫苗接種會降低[[群体免疫|群体免疫]]的效果。例如麻疹疫苗是在九個月及十二個月時接種，在兩次接種之間沒有母體抗體的期間<!--（before which the vaccine often fails to {{le|seroconversion|血清轉換|seroconvert}}）-->以及有自然感染的可能，表示這段時間的嬰兒仍非常脆弱，容易受到感染。若所有的兒童都在規定時間接種疫苗，群体免疫可以減輕感染的可能性。在傳染病爆發或是即將爆發時，大規模的疫苗接種是最可以被接受的增加群体免疫力方式。當研發了新的疫苗，大規模接種也可以讓有免疫力的人數量迅速增加，因此提昇群体免疫力<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Mass vaccination: when and why|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16989261/|last=Heymann|first=D. L.|last2=Aylward|first2=R. B.|date=2006|journal=Current Topics in Microbiology and Immunology|doi=10.1007/3-540-36583-4_1|volume=304|pages=1–16|issn=0070-217X|pmid=16989261|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225093217/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16989261/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

增加群体免疫力也有助於一些免疫能力較弱的人。一些兒童因免疫能力較弱，無法接種特定疫苗，因此要靠其他人接種疫苗來讓不容易感染對應的疾病。若免疫能力較弱的兒童周圍都是沒有接種疫苗且有對應疾病的人，這個兒童很可能會感染這種疾病，而他感染後的結果顯然會比免疫能力正常的兒童要嚴重。提昇群体免疫力及（對有正常免疫系統的人）強制疫苗接種可以減少這類的風險<ref>{{Cite web|title=How Vaccines Work|url=https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/parents/why-vaccinate/vaccine-decision.html|accessdate=2020-12-19|date=2020-06-16|last=CDC|work=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|language=en-us|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319130244/https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/parents/why-vaccinate/vaccine-decision.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 經濟有效===
和急性及慢性疾病的治療比較起來，常用的疫苗是促進健康的方法中，經濟有效而且是預防性的方法。美國2001年針對七種疾病的定期{{le|疫苗定期接種|vaccination schedule}}，估計在每個生育年度節省了四百億美元，其中包括一百億美元的直接[[健康经济学|健康成本]]、而社會為了這些疫苗注射的效益約為成本的16.5倍<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Economic Evaluation of the 7-Vaccine Routine Childhood Immunization Schedule in the United States, 2001|url=http://archpedi.ama-assn.org/cgi/content/full/159/12/1136|last=Zhou|first=Fangjun|last2=Santoli|first2=Jeanne|date=2005-12-01|journal=Archives of Pediatrics & Adolescent Medicine|issue=12|doi=10.1001/archpedi.159.12.1136|volume=159|pages=1136|language=en|issn=1072-4710|last3=Messonnier|first3=Mark L.|last4=Yusuf|first4=Hussain R.|last5=Shefer|first5=Abigail|last6=Chu|first6=Susan Y.|last7=Rodewald|first7=Lance|last8=Harpaz|first8=Rafael|access-date=2016-09-26|archive-date=2012-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120428121736/http://archpedi.ama-assn.org/cgi/content/full/159/12/1136|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===必要性===
當疫苗接種計劃成功了降低了疾病的威脅時，也可能降低了某特定文化下，大眾對疾病影響的印象。這種情形下，家長可能會覺得兒女不接種疫苗，其實也不會有什麼影響<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Fine PE, Clarkson JA |date=December 1986 |title=Individual versus public priorities in the determination of optimal vaccination policies |journal=American Journal of Epidemiology |volume=124 |issue=6 |pages=1012–20 |doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.aje.a114471 |pmid=3096132}}</ref>。疫苗接種有[[群體免疫|群體免疫]]效果，若有夠多的人接種疫苗，極少數無法接種疫苗的人也會因為周圍的人有施打疫苗而受益。但是若太多的人不願施打疫苗，希望[[搭便车问题|搭便车]]，讓施打疫苗的比例降低到一定程度，也就沒有了群體免疫效果<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Buttenheim AM, Asch DA |date=December 2013 |title=Making vaccine refusal less of a free ride |journal=Human Vaccines & Immunotherapeutics |volume=9 |issue=12 |pages=2674–75 |doi=10.4161/hv.26676 |pmc=4162060 |pmid=24088616}}</ref>。依照美國社會學家Jennifer Reich的論點，那些認為疫苗有效，但不願意讓兒女施打疫苗的父母，只要適當的接觸他們，提供正確的資訊，他們最容易改變心意，讓兒女施打疫苗<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vox.com/first-person/2019/5/8/18535944/jessica-biel-measles-2019-outbreak-anti-vax |title=I've talked to dozens of parents about why they don't vaccinate. Here's what they told me. |last=Reich |first=Jennifer |author-link=Jennifer Reich |date=June 13, 2019 |website=Vox |access-date=July 5, 2019 |archive-date=2021-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210903043934/https://www.vox.com/first-person/2019/5/8/18535944/jessica-biel-measles-2019-outbreak-anti-vax |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 安全性 ==
有些反疫苗人士公開反對疫苗的快速發展對公共衛生的助益，或是存有[[陰謀論|陰謀論]]<ref name="wolfesharp"/>，不過較常見的是對疫苗安全性的質疑<ref name="LancetID">{{Cite journal |last=The Lancet Infectious Diseases |date=April 2007 |title=Tackling negative perceptions towards vaccination |journal=The Lancet Infectious Diseases |volume=7 |issue=4 |pages=235 |doi=10.1016/S1473-3099(07)70057-9 |pmid=17376373}}</ref>。正如許多醫學治療一様，疫苗有可能會引發嚴重的併發症，例如嚴重的過敏反應<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/vac-gen/side-effects.htm#mmr|title = Possible Side-effects from Vaccines|accessdate = 2014-01-03|publisher = Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|date = 2013-08-26|archive-date = 2021-03-18|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318012844/https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/vac-gen/side-effects.htm#mmr|dead-url = no}}</ref>，不過不同於其他醫學治療的是，疫苗是給健康的人施打，因此也會期待有比較高的安全標準<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Vaccine Safety: Current and Future Challenges|url=http://www.healio.com/doiresolver?doi=10.3928/0090-4481-19980701-11|last=Chen|first=Robert T|last2=Hibbs|first2=Beth|date=1998-07-01|journal=Pediatric Annals|issue=7|doi=10.3928/0090-4481-19980701-11|volume=27|pages=445–455|language=en|issn=0090-4481|access-date=2022-01-18|archive-date=2018-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604024826/https://www.healio.com/doiresolver?doi=10.3928%2F0090-4481-19980701-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有些疫苗有可能產生嚴重的併發症，但其比例其實相當少，而且其併發症風險比未施打疫苗時，可能罹患疾病的風險要小很多<ref name="CDC: common misconceptions" />。隨著疫苗注射計劃的進展以及疾病發生率的下降，公眾的注意力開始從疾病本身的風險轉移到疫苗的風險<ref name="BH">{{Cite journal|title=Adverse events following immunization: perception and evidence:|url=http://journals.lww.com/00001432-200706000-00002|last=Bonhoeffer|first=Jan|last2=Heininger|first2=Ulrich|date=2007-06|journal=Current Opinion in Infectious Diseases|issue=3|doi=10.1097/QCO.0b013e32811ebfb0|volume=20|pages=237–246|language=en|issn=0951-7375}}</ref>，這也變成衛生主管機關要讓大眾繼續支持疫苗計劃的一大挑戰<ref>{{Cite web|title=Why Does the Vaccine/Autism Controversy Live On?|url=https://www.discovermagazine.com/health/why-does-the-vaccine-autism-controversy-live-on|accessdate=2020-12-20|work=Discover Magazine|language=en|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609091529/http://discovermagazine.com/2009/jun/06-why-does-vaccine-autism-controversy-live-on|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

一些疫苗計劃非常成功，讓疾病變的非常罕見，對於疫苗猶豫的人而言，在評估疫苗風險和助益時，反而造成了不正確的{{le|判斷和決策中的啟發|Heuristics in judgment and decision-making|啟發式思考}}<ref name="Jacobson2015">{{Cite journal |last1=Jacobson |first1=RM |last2=St Sauver |first2=JL |last3=Finney Rutten |first3=LJ |date=November 2015 |title=Vaccine Hesitancy |journal=Mayo Clinic Proceedings |volume=90 |issue=11 |pages=1562–68 |doi=10.1016/j.mayocp.2015.09.006 |pmid=26541249|doi-access=free}}</ref>。當某種疾病（例如[[流感嗜血桿菌|流感嗜血桿菌]]）的盛行率降低時，人們因為不熟悉此種疾病，不再意識到該疾病的嚴重性，因此變的自滿<ref name="Jacobson2015" />。個人缺乏有關這些疾病的經驗，也讓人降低所認知到該疾病的風險，也降低所認知到免疫的助益<ref name="Marshall2013" />。相反的，也有些疾病（例如[[流行性感冒|流行性感冒]]）非常普遍，就算有清楚的科學證據證實此疾病對人類健康有很大的威脅，但疫苗猶豫者會誤以為疾病的威脅性不大<ref name="Jacobson2015" />。[[不作为偏误|不作为偏误]]和[[確認偏誤|確認偏誤]]也都會造成疫苗猶豫<ref name="Jacobson2015" /><ref name="McClure2017">{{Cite journal |last1=McClure |first1=CC |last2=Cataldi |first2=JR |last3=O'Leary |first3=ST |date=August 2017 |title=Vaccine Hesitancy: Where We Are and Where We Are Going |journal=Clinical Therapeutics |volume=39 |issue=8 |pages=1550–62 |doi=10.1016/j.clinthera.2017.07.003 |pmid=28774498|doi-access=free}}</ref>。

有許多不同有關疫苗的疑慮，目前這些疑慮都沒有實證上的支持<ref name="Marshall2013">{{Cite journal |last=Marshall |first=GS |date=2013 |title=Roots of vaccine hesitancy |journal=S D Med |volume=Spec no |pages=52–57 |pmid=23444592}}</ref>。有關疫苗安全性的疑慮有固定的模式。一開始是一些研究者認為某種未知原因醫學狀況的發生率增加是因為疫苗的副作用所造成，同一群研究者的初始研究及後續研究在方法論上都有問題，多半是數量不足的受控或非受控{{le|病例系列|case series}}。有關疫苗的副作用過早公布，在受到疫苗副作用影響的人身上產生共鳴，而且低估了放棄疫苗接種可能帶來的潛在危害。其他研究團體設法要複製初始的實驗結果，但就無法成功複製。最後需要再花許多年的時間才能讓大家對疫苗重新恢復信心<ref name="BH" />。歸因於疫苗的不良反應一般都是來源未知、[[发病率|发病率]]上升、有一些{{le|生物合理性|biological plausibility}}、發生時間接近疫苗接種的時間，而且有可怕的後果<ref>{{Cite journal|title="All manner of ills": The features of serious diseases attributed to vaccination|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19879997|last=Leask|first=Julie|last2=Chapman|first2=Simon|date=2010-04-09|journal=Vaccine|issue=17|doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2009.10.042|volume=28|pages=3066–3070|issn=1873-2518|pmid=19879997|last3=Cooper Robbins|first3=Spring Chenoa|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210811013534/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19879997/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。幾乎所有的例子中，疫苗對公共衛生的影響都受到不同文化的限制，因此各國擔心的疫苗及副作用可能也有不同：可能英語系國家擔心疫苗造成自閉症，法語地區擔心另一種疫苗造成多發性硬化，而尼日利亚人担心其他疫苗会导致不孕<ref>{{cite book|last=Goldacre|first=Ben|title=Bad Science|url=https://archive.org/details/badscience0000gold_e1h0|year=2009|publisher=Fourth Estate|location=London|isbn=9780007284870|pages=[https://archive.org/details/badscience0000gold_e1h0/page/292 292]–294}}</ref>。

=== 硫柳汞 ===
{{Main|硫柳汞和疫苗}}
[[硫柳汞|硫柳汞]]是[[抗真菌药|抗真菌药]]，在多劑量的疫苗（一個疫苗小瓶中的劑量是多人份的劑量，需為幾個人注射後才會用完）中可以避免疫苗受到污染<ref name="Baker">{{Cite journal|title=Mercury, vaccines, and autism: one controversy, three histories|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18172138|last=Baker|first=Jeffrey P.|date=2008-02|journal=American Journal of Public Health|issue=2|doi=10.2105/AJPH.2007.113159|volume=98|pages=244–253|issn=1541-0048|pmc=2376879|pmid=18172138|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227065916/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18172138/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不過硫柳汞雖功效良好，但因為其中含[[汞|汞]]，在人體代謝後會分解為[[乙基汞|乙基汞]] C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub>Hg<sup>+</sup>和[[硫代水杨酸|硫代水杨酸]]，在使用上有造成{{le|硫柳汞爭議|Thiomersal controversy|相關爭議}}<ref name=T-in-vaccines>{{cite web |date=June 3, 2008 |url=https://www.fda.gov/cber/vaccine/thimerosal.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080726010009/https://www.fda.gov/cber/vaccine/thimerosal.htm |archive-date=July 26, 2008|url-status=dead |access-date=July 25, 2008 |title=Thimerosal in vaccines |publisher=Center for Biologics Evaluation and Research, U.S. Food and Drug Administration}}</ref><ref name=cber2019 />。1999年時[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国疾病控制与预防中心]]（CDC）及[[美國小兒科學會|美國小兒科學會]]（AAP）基於減少可能風險的[[預防原則|預防原則]]下，要求疫苗製造商儘快在疫苗中停用硫柳汞。現在在所有美國及歐洲的常見疫苗中都沒有硫柳汞，只有在一些[[季節性流感疫苗|季節性流感疫苗]]中才可能出現<ref name="Offit">{{Cite journal|title=Thimerosal and vaccines--a cautionary tale|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17898096|last=Offit|first=Paul A.|date=2007-09-27|journal=The New England Journal of Medicine|issue=13|doi=10.1056/NEJMp078187|volume=357|pages=1278–1279|issn=1533-4406|pmid=17898096|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308121605/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17898096/|dead-url=no}}</ref>（因為製造過程關係，仍然會有痕量的殘留，最高殘留量約1μg，約美國成人每日平均汞攝取量的15%，也是[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]每日容許攝取量的2.5%<ref name=cber2019>{{Cite journal |author=Center for Biologics Evaluation and Research |date=April 5, 2019 |title=Thimerosal and Vaccines |url=https://www.fda.gov/vaccines-blood-biologics/safety-availability-biologics/thimerosal-and-vaccines |journal=FDA |publisher=fda.gov |access-date=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2019-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419070239/https://www.fda.gov/biologicsbloodvaccines/safetyavailability/vaccinesafety/ucm096228 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Mercury Exposure and Children’s Health|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3096006/|last=Bose-O’Reilly|first=Stephan|last2=McCarty|first2=Kathleen M.|date=2010-9|journal=Current problems in pediatric and adolescent health care|issue=8|doi=10.1016/j.cppeds.2010.07.002|volume=40|pages=186–215|issn=1538-5442|pmc=3096006|pmid=20816346|last3=Steckling|first3=Nadine|last4=Lettmeier|first4=Beate|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210317034410/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3096006/|dead-url=no}}</ref>）。此一舉動開始讓大眾關注硫柳汞是否是造成自閉症的原因<ref name="Offit" />，不過目前認為硫柳汞不是造成自閉症的原因，因為自從兒童疫苗中停用硫柳汞後，自閉症發生率仍然繼續的增加<ref name="Gerber">{{Cite journal|title=Vaccines and Autism: A Tale of Shifting Hypotheses|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2908388/|last=Gerber|first=Jeffrey S.|last2=Offit|first2=Paul A.|date=2009-02-15|journal=Clinical infectious diseases : an official publication of the Infectious Diseases Society of America|issue=4|doi=10.1086/596476|volume=48|pages=456–461|issn=1058-4838|pmc=2908388|pmid=19128068|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313135241/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2908388/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。目前還沒有可靠的科學證據可以證實接觸硫柳汞是導致自閉症的因素之一<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Immunizations and autism: a review of the literature|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17168158|last=Doja|first=Asif|last2=Roberts|first2=Wendy|date=2006-11|journal=The Canadian Journal of Neurological Sciences. Le Journal Canadien Des Sciences Neurologiques|issue=4|doi=10.1017/s031716710000528x|volume=33|pages=341–346|issn=0317-1671|pmid=17168158|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319170712/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17168158/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2000年起，有些美國家長認為是疫苗中的硫柳汞造成他們小孩的自閉症，希望從聯邦基金中取得法定的賠償<ref name="Sugarman">{{Cite journal|title=Cases in vaccine court--legal battles over vaccines and autism|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17898095|last=Sugarman|first=Stephen D.|date=2007-09-27|journal=The New England Journal of Medicine|issue=13|doi=10.1056/NEJMp078168|volume=357|pages=1275–1277|issn=1533-4406|pmid=17898095|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225100121/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17898095/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{le|醫學研究組織|Institute of Medicine}}（IOM）委員會在2004年認為含硫柳汞的疫苗和自閉症之間沒有因果關係<ref name="ISRC">{{Cite book |url=http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=10997 |title=Immunization Safety Review: Vaccines and Autism |last=Immunization Safety Review Committee |publisher=The National Academies Press |year=2004 |isbn=978-0-309-09237-1 |doi=10.17226/10997 |pmid=20669467 |access-date=2016-09-30 |archive-date=2012-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120704161757/http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=10997 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。疫苗中使用的硫柳汞濃度從0.001%到0.01%不等<ref name="FDAThiomersalTuna" />。0.5 mL的疫苗，若其中含有0.01%的硫柳汞，其汞劑量為25μg，大約和三盎司[[鮪魚|鮪魚]]罐頭中的含汞量相當<ref name="FDAThiomersalTuna">{{Cite web |url=https://www.fda.gov/vaccines-blood-biologics/safety-availability-biologics/thimerosal-and-vaccines#pres |title=Thimerosal and Vaccines |date=April 5, 2019 |website=fda.gov |publisher=U.S. Food and Drug Administration |access-date=2020-12-20 |archive-date=2019-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419070239/https://www.fda.gov/biologicsbloodvaccines/safetyavailability/vaccinesafety/ucm096228#pres |dead-url=no }}</ref>，有強而有力的同行評審科學證據支持含硫柳汞疫苗的安全性<ref name="FDAThiomersalTuna" />。

===麻腮風三聯疫苗===
{{Main|麻疹腮腺炎德國麻疹混合疫苗爭議}}
1998年時{{le|安德魯·韋克菲爾德|Andrew Wakefield}}及多名共同作者在《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|柳葉刀]]》期刊發表論文（此論文後來被期刊撤回），其中提到12名兒童在注射[[麻腮风三联疫苗|麻腮风三联疫苗]]後，就出現[[自閉症光譜|自閉症光譜]]中的一些症狀，從此麻腮风三联疫苗就成為英國相關爭議的焦點之一<ref>{{Cite journal|title=RETRACTED: Ileal-lymphoid-nodular hyperplasia, non-specific colitis, and pervasive developmental disorder in children|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673697110960|last=Wakefield|first=Aj|last2=Murch|first2=Sh|date=1998-02|journal=The Lancet|issue=9103|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(97)11096-0|volume=351|pages=637–641|language=en|last3=Anthony|first3=A|last4=Linnell|first4=J|last5=Casson|first5=Dm|last6=Malik|first6=M|last7=Berelowitz|first7=M|last8=Dhillon|first8=Ap|last9=Thomson|first9=Ma|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308171628/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673697110960|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在1998年的研討會中，韋克菲爾德認為若三種疫苗分開注射，而不是一起注射，可能會比較安全。不過論文中沒有有關此一論點的支持，而隨後許多同行評審的研究也沒有發現疫苗和自閉症之間的關係<ref name="NHS">{{cite web|title=MMR: myths and truths|url=http://www.mmrthefacts.nhs.uk/basics/truths.php|accessdate=2007-09-03|author=National Health Service|year=2004|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913173824/http://www.mmrthefacts.nhs.uk/basics/truths.php|archivedate=2008-09-13|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。之後發現韋克菲爾德有獲得資金援助，資金來源是向疫苗製造商提出訴訟的訴訟當事人，而韋克菲爾德並未將此[[利益衝突|利益衝突]]的情形告知同事或醫學主管機關<ref>{{cite news|author= Deer B|title= Revealed: MMR research scandal|work= The Sunday Times|date= 2004-02-22|url= http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/health/article1027603.ece|accessdate= 2007-09-23|archive-date= 2021-10-30|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211030000947/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=自闭症，不是三联疫苗的错|url=http://www.nbweekly.com/news/tech/200903/9496.aspx|publisher=南都周刊|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161006041812/http://www.nbweekly.com/news/tech/200903/9496.aspx|archivedate=2016-10-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。若《柳葉刀》期刊編輯知道有此情形，韋克菲爾德的論文也就不會在雜誌上發表<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The lessons of MMR|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673604157140|last=Horton|first=Richard|date=2004-03|journal=The Lancet|issue=9411|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(04)15714-0|volume=363|pages=747–749|language=en|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2020-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200623070534/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673604157140|dead-url=no}}</ref>。韋克菲爾德因為其科學證據的問題飽受批評，而且普遍認為他的論文造成疫苗注射率的下降<ref>{{Cite news|title=Doctors issue plea over MMR jab|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/5118166.stm|date=2006-06-26|accessdate=2020-12-20|language=en-GB|archive-date=2018-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914211517/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/5118166.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。（在此研究發表後，英國的疫苗注射率降到原來的80%）<ref name="Alazraki11">{{cite news|author=Alazraki M|title=The Autism Vaccine Fraud: Dr. Wakefield's Costly Lie to Society|newspaper=DailyFinance, AOL Money & Finance|date=2011-01-12|url=http://www.dailyfinance.com/2011/01/12/autism-vaccine-fraud-wakefield-cost-money-deaths/|accessdate=2016-10-21|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111027104603/http://www.dailyfinance.com/2011/01/12/autism-vaccine-fraud-wakefield-cost-money-deaths/|archivedate=2011-10-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Measles outbreak worsens in US after unvaccinated woman visits Disneyland|url=http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/14/measles-outbreak-spreads-unvaccinated-woman-disneyland|accessdate=2015-06-01|date=2015-01-19|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309141158/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/14/measles-outbreak-spreads-unvaccinated-woman-disneyland|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而其研究也有[[利益衝突|利益衝突]]的道德問題<ref name="paid_children">{{Cite news|title=MMR scare doctor 'paid children'|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/6289166.stm|date=2007-07-16|accessdate=2020-12-20|language=en-GB|archive-date=2017-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908062009/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/6289166.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。疫苗和自閉症相關性論文的共同作者有12人，有10名在2004年宣佈撤消在該篇論文中的署名<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Retraction of an interpretation|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673604157152|last=Murch|first=Simon H|last2=Anthony|first2=Andrew|date=2004-03|journal=The Lancet|issue=9411|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(04)15715-2|volume=363|pages=750|language=en|last3=Casson|first3=David H|last4=Malik|first4=Mohsin|last5=Berelowitz|first5=Mark|last6=Dhillon|first6=Amar P|last7=Thomson|first7=Michael A|last8=Valentine|first8=Alan|last9=Davies|first9=Susan E|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226231945/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673604157152|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2010年時，《柳葉刀》期刊編輯正式的撤回此一論文<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Retraction—Ileal-lymphoid-nodular hyperplasia, non-specific colitis, and pervasive developmental disorder in children|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673610601754|last=The Editors of The Lancet|date=2010-02|journal=The Lancet|issue=9713|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(10)60175-4|volume=375|pages=445|language=en|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308111724/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0140673610601754|dead-url=no}}</ref>。韋克菲爾德因為在該篇論文中有意的偽造研究資訊，被[[醫學總會_(英國)|英國醫學總會]]取消英國註冊醫師資格<ref name="gmc-uk_Wakefield_SPM">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmc-uk.org/Wakefield_SPM_and_SANCTION.pdf_32595267.pdf|format=PDF|title=General Medical Council, Fitness to Practise Panel Hearing, 24 May 2010, Andrew Wakefield, Determination of Serious Professional Misconduct|accessdate=2011-09-18|publisher=General Medical Council|dead-url=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130512115524/http://www.gmc-uk.org/Wakefield_SPM_and_SANCTION.pdf_32595267.pdf|archivedate=2013-05-12}}</ref>，並且禁止在英國從事醫療行為<ref name="MeikleBoseley">{{Cite web|title=MMR row doctor Andrew Wakefield struck off register|url=http://www.theguardian.com/society/2010/may/24/mmr-doctor-andrew-wakefield-struck-off|accessdate=2020-12-20|date=2010-05-24|work=the Guardian|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223214817/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2010/may/24/mmr-doctor-andrew-wakefield-struck-off|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

疾病预防控制中心<ref>{{Cite web|title=Safety Information for Measles, Mumps, Rubella, Varicella Vaccines {{!}} CDC|url=https://www.cdc.gov/vaccinesafety/vaccines/mmrv-vaccine.html|accessdate=2020-12-20|date=2020-09-09|work=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|archive-date=2021-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210318001601/https://www.cdc.gov/vaccinesafety/vaccines/mmrv-vaccine.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[美国国家科学院|美国国家科学院]]的醫學研究組織<ref name="ISRC" />、以及[[國民保健署|英國國民保健署]]<ref>[http://www.mmrthefacts.nhs.uk/ MMR Fact Sheet] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070615000359/http://www.mmrthefacts.nhs.uk/|date=2007-06-15}}, from the United Kingdom National Health Service. Retrieved 2007-06-13.</ref>都認為無法證實麻腮風三聯疫苗和自閉症之間有關。{{le|Cochrane图书馆|Cochrane Library}}進行的系統研究也認為麻腮風三聯疫苗及自閉症之間沒有可信的關連，而麻腮風三聯疫苗可以預防會造成許多傷亡及併發症的疾病，因此大眾對三聯疫苗缺乏信任一事已經傷害了公共衛生，而大部份有關麻腮風三聯疫苗設計以及安全性结果的研究是不充份的<ref name="pmid22336803">{{Cite journal|title=Vaccines for measles, mumps and rubella in children|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22336803|last=Demicheli|first=Vittorio|last2=Rivetti|first2=Alessandro|date=2012-02-15|journal=The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews|issue=2|doi=10.1002/14651858.CD004407.pub3|pages=CD004407|issn=1469-493X|pmc=6458016|pmid=22336803|last3=Debalini|first3=Maria Grazia|last4=Di Pietrantonj|first4=Carlo|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2020-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201231060706/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22336803/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其他的文獻探討也同意此一論點，有研究發現就算是在高風險的自閉症手足身上，也沒有發現疫苗和自閉症之間的關係<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=DeStefano |first1=Frank |last2=Shimabukuro |first2=Tom T. |date=2019-04-15 |title=The MMR Vaccine and Autism |journal=Annual Review of Virology |volume=6 |issue=1 |pages=585–600 |doi=10.1146/annurev-virology-092818-015515 |issn=2327-0578 |pmc=6768751 |pmid=30986133}}</ref>。

2009年時《[[星期日泰晤士報|星期日泰晤士報]]》報導，韋克菲爾德在其1998年的論文中修改病患數據並且誤報其結果，製造和自閉症之間的關聯性<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/health/article5683671.ece|title=MMR doctor Andrew Wakefield fixed data on autism|author=Deer B|work=Sunday Times|date=2009-02-08|accessdate=2009-02-09|archive-date=2011-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006040554/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/health/article5683671.ece|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2011年[[英國醫學期刊|英國醫學期刊]]說明韋克菲爾德如何偽偽造數據，以達到預期的結論<ref>{{Cite journal|title=How the case against the MMR vaccine was fixed|url=https://www.bmj.com/content/342/bmj.c5347|last=Deer|first=Brian|date=2011-01-06|journal=BMJ|doi=10.1136/bmj.c5347|volume=342|language=en|issn=0959-8138|pmid=21209059|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313011010/https://www.bmj.com/content/342/bmj.c5347|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此期刊的評論認為韋克菲爾德的研究是「复杂的[[詐騙|詐騙]]」，降低了疫苗接種率，造成上百萬的兒童置身危險之中，而且讓許多的精力及資金轉向，沒有去研究真正造成自閉症的原因<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Wakefield’s article linking MMR vaccine and autism was fraudulent|url=https://www.bmj.com/content/342/bmj.c7452|last=Godlee|first=Fiona|last2=Smith|first2=Jane|date=2011-01-06|journal=BMJ|doi=10.1136/bmj.c7452|volume=342|language=en|issn=0959-8138|pmid=21209060|last3=Marcovitch|first3=Harvey|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307120045/https://www.bmj.com/content/342/bmj.c7452|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

美國的{{le|疫苗法庭|Vaccine court|美国国家疫苗伤害赔偿计划}}在2009年2月12日的特别法庭审查裁定，自閉症兒童的父母認為疫苗造成子女自閉症的論點不成立，無權獲得賠償<ref>Vaccine court and autism:
*{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/02/12/autism.vaccines/index.html?iref=allsearch|title=Vaccine didn't cause autism, court rules|date=2009-02-12|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2009-02-12|archive-date=2019-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204231459/http://www.cnn.com/2009/HEALTH/02/12/autism.vaccines/index.html?iref=allsearch|dead-url=no}}
*{{cite court|litigants = Theresa Cedillo and Michael Cedillo, as parents and natural guardians of Michelle Cedillo vs. Secretary of Health and Human Services|vol = 98-916V|court = United States Court of Federal Claims|date = 2009-02-12|url=ftp://autism.uscfc.uscourts.gov/autism/vaccine/Hastings-Cedillo.pdf}}</ref>。

=== 疫苗過載 ===
“疫苗過載”（{{lang|en|Vaccine overload}}）指同時給予兒童多種疫苗將減弱其免疫系統，引致不良反應甚至死亡<ref name="Hilton">{{Cite journal|title='Combined vaccines are like a sudden onslaught to the body's immune system': parental concerns about vaccine 'overload' and 'immune-vulnerability'|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16581162|last=Hilton|first=Shona|last2=Petticrew|first2=Mark|date=2006-05-15|journal=Vaccine|issue=20|doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2006.03.003|volume=24|pages=4321–4327|issn=0264-410X|pmid=16581162|last3=Hunt|first3=Kate|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301154752/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16581162/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此論點與科學證據不符<ref name="Gerber" />，不過有些自閉症兒童的家長仍認為疫苗過載會引發自閉症<ref>{{Cite web|title=Vaccine phobia runs deep|url=https://www.thestar.com/life/health_wellness/news_research/2009/10/30/vaccine_phobia_runs_deep.html|accessdate=2020-12-20|date=2009-10-30|work=thestar.com|language=en|archive-date=2012-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019160659/http://www.thestar.com/news/article/718829|dead-url=no}}</ref>，使他們延後甚至不為兒童接種疫苗<ref name="Hilton" /><ref>{{Cite journal|title=An internet-based survey on parental attitudes towards immunization|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16784799|last=Heininger|first=Ulrich|date=2006-09-11|journal=Vaccine|issue=37-39|doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2006.05.029|volume=24|pages=6351–6355|issn=0264-410X|pmid=16784799|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206203301/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16784799/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

疫苗過載此誤解有多種錯誤<ref name="Gerber" />。須接種的疫苗雖然在近數十年有所增量，但疫苗設計亦同時進步，減低了疫苗的免疫負荷，例如：美國2009年給兩歲兒童接種的疫苗有14種，1980年給兩歲兒童接種7種疫苗，但前者的免疫成份不到後者的十分之一<ref name="Gerber"/>。2013年的研究在兩歲兒童接種的疫苗中找不到[[抗原|抗原]]數量與自閉症的關聯。研究針對1,008名兒童，其中有四分之一診斷有自閉症，隊列研究是在1994年至1999年做的，當時的疫苗接種計劃中會包括超過3,000種抗原（一劑[[百白破疫苗|百白破疫苗]]的份量）。2012年的疫苗接種計劃中的疫苗種類更多，但二歲兒童所會接觸到的抗原只有315種<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/emilywillingham/2013/03/29/vaccines-not-linked-to-autism-again/ |title=Vaccines Not Linked To Autism. Again |last=Willingham, Emily |author-link=Emily Willingham |date=March 29, 2013 |website=Forbes |access-date=April 4, 2013 |archive-date=2019-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203211139/https://www.forbes.com/sites/emilywillingham/2013/03/29/vaccines-not-linked-to-autism-again/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |author-link=Frank DeStefano |vauthors=DeStefano F, Price CS, Weintraub ES |date=August 2013 |title=Increasing exposure to antibody-stimulating proteins and polysaccharides in vaccines is not associated with risk of autism |url=http://www.jpeds.com/webfiles/images/journals/ympd/JPEDSDeStefano.pdf |journal=The Journal of Pediatrics |volume=163 |issue=2 |pages=561–77 |citeseerx=10.1.1.371.2592 |doi=10.1016/j.jpeds.2013.02.001 |pmid=23545349 |access-date=2021-12-11 |archive-date=2014-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140923222908/http://www.jpeds.com/webfiles/images/journals/ympd/JPEDSDeStefano.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。對於兒童而言，平常一年內會接觸到的抗原數量比疫苗中的要多<ref name="Gerber" />。兒童常見的疾病（例如發燒和[[中耳炎|中耳炎]]）對免疫系統的挑戰比疫苗還要大<ref>Immune challenges:
*{{cite journal |vauthors=Murphy TF |title=Branhamella catarrhalis: epidemiology, surface antigenic structure, and immune response |journal=Microbiological Reviews |volume=60 |issue=2 |pages=267–79 |date=June 1996 |doi=10.1128/MMBR.60.2.267-279.1996 |pmid=8801433 |pmc=239443 |url=}}
*{{cite journal |vauthors=Sloyer JL, Howie VM, Ploussard JH, Ammann AJ, Austrian R, Johnston RB |title=Immune response to acute otitis media in children. I. Serotypes isolated and serum and middle ear fluid antibody in pneumococcal otitis media |journal=Infection and Immunity |volume=9 |issue=6 |pages=1028–32 |date=June 1974 |doi=10.1128/IAI.9.6.1028-1032.1974 |pmid=4151506 |pmc=414928 |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_infection-and-immunity_1974-06_9_6/page/1028}}</ref>，而且研究指出就算是同時注射多種疾苗，也不會減弱免疫系統<ref name="Gerber" />或是破壞免疫力<ref>Vaccine burden:
*{{cite journal |vauthors=Miller E, Andrews N, Waight P, Taylor B |title=Bacterial infections, immune overload, and MMR vaccine. Measles, mumps, and rubella |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_archives-of-disease-in-childhood_2003-03_88_3/page/222 |journal=Archives of Disease in Childhood |volume=88 |issue=3 |pages=222–23 |date=March 2003 |pmid=12598383 |pmc=1719482 |doi=10.1136/adc.88.3.222}}
*{{cite journal |vauthors=Hviid A, Wohlfahrt J, Stellfeld M, Melbye M |title=Childhood vaccination and nontargeted infectious disease hospitalization |journal=JAMA |volume=294 |issue=6 |pages=699–705 |date=August 2005 |pmid=16091572 |doi=10.1001/jama.294.6.699 | doi-access = free}}</ref>。疫苗過載的假說缺乏實證的支持，而且研究所得的結果和此假說矛盾，因此所得的結論是目前建議的疫苗接種計劃不會有「過載」情形，也不會減弱免疫系統<ref name="BH" /><ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Gregson AL, Edelman R |date=November 2003 |title=Does antigenic overload exist? The role of multiple immunizations in infants |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_immunology-and-allergy-clinics-of-north-america_2003-11_23_4/page/649 |journal=Immunology and Allergy Clinics of North America |volume=23 |issue=4 |pages=649–64 |doi=10.1016/S0889-8561(03)00097-3 |pmid=14753385}}</ref><ref name="Hackett-Offit" /><ref name="Schneeweiss" />。

以不讓兒童接種疫苗為基礎的實驗，有實驗道德的問題<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Deen JL, Clemens JD |date=November 2006 |title=Issues in the design and implementation of vaccine trials in less developed countries |journal=Nature Reviews. Drug Discovery |volume=5 |issue=11 |pages=932–40 |doi=10.1038/nrd2159 |pmid=17080029 |s2cid=413230}}</ref>，觀察性研究也可能會因為疫苗接種不足的兒童尋求醫療的行為而造成研究的[[干擾因素|干擾]]。因此，沒有研究直接比較有接種疫苗兒童和未接種疫苗兒童的自閉症比例。不過，疫苗過載的概念在生物學上是不合信的，不論是否接種疫苗，兒童對和疫苗無關疾病的免疫反應是相同的，而且自閉症不是免疫介導的疾病，因此，自閉症會因為免疫系統過載而引發的論點，和目前所知自閉症的{{link-en|發病機制|pathogenesis}}衝突。目前證據的效力，已足以駁斥疫苗會造成自閉症的想法<ref name="Gerber" />。

===產前感染===
有證據表示[[精神分裂症|精神分裂症]]和胎兒在母體時暴露在[[風疹|風疹]]、[[流行性感冒|流行性感冒]]和[[弓蟲症|弓蟲症]]感染的條件有關。例如，有研究指出若在懷孕的前三個月有流行性感冒，其精神分裂症風險會增加七倍。這對公共衛生會產生影響，例如預防感染的策略，包括接種疫苗、保持衛生，若針對弓蟲症的話，還包括[[抗细菌药|抗细菌药]]<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Fineberg AM, Ellman LM |date=May 2013 |title=Inflammatory cytokines and neurological and neurocognitive alterations in the course of schizophrenia |journal=Biological Psychiatry |volume=73 |issue=10 |pages=951–66 |doi=10.1016/j.biopsych.2013.01.001 |pmc=3641168 |pmid=23414821}}</ref>。依照動物模型的研究，精神分裂症和母體因為抗原產生的免疫反應有可能的相關性，而2009年的回顧研究認為目前還沒有足夠證據來建議在懷孕的前三個月施行[[季節性流感疫苗|季節性流感疫苗]]，但在三個月後仍建議施打，若在已有疾情，或是孕婦在特殊條件下，仍建議施打<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Skowronski DM, De Serres G |date=July 2009 |title=Is routine influenza immunization warranted in early pregnancy? |journal=Vaccine |volume=27 |issue=35 |pages=4754–70 |doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2009.03.079 |pmid=19515466}}</ref>。美國疾病管制與預防中心的{{link-en|免疫實踐諮詢委員會|Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices}}、{{link-en|美國婦產科醫學會|American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists}}以及{{link-en|美國家庭醫師學會|American Academy of Family Physicians}}基於以下理由，仍建議孕婦施打流感疫苗<ref name="ACIP2007" />：
*後面六個月有流感相關嚴重併發症的高風險。
*相較於未懷孕的女性，孕婦因為流感住院的比率會比較高
*施打疫苗有可能將母體的流感抗體轉移給胎兒，也可以保護胎兒
*許多研究指出疫苗對孕婦和胎兒都無害。

雖然如此，2005年美國孕婦中只有15%有施打流感疫苗<ref name="ACIP2007">{{Cite journal |vauthors=Fiore AE, Shay DK, Haber P, Iskander JK, Uyeki TM, Mootrey G, Bresee JS, Cox NJ |date=July 2007 |title=Prevention and control of influenza. Recommendations of the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices (ACIP), 2007 |url=https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/rr5606a1.htm |journal=MMWR. Recommendations and Reports |volume=56 |issue=RR-6 |pages=1–54 |pmid=17625497 |access-date=2022-01-07 |archive-date=2019-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191111043647/https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/rr5606a1.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===對其成分的疑慮===
許多疫苗會用鋁化合物為[[疫苗佐劑|疫苗佐劑]]，以增強疫苗的效果。鋁似乎可以模擬少量的組織損傷，甚至造成少量的組織損傷，讓身體免疫系統認為是嚴重的感染，會有比較顯著的反應，也讓免疫應答的效果可以加長<ref name="Baylor">{{Cite journal|title=Aluminum salts in vaccines--US perspective|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12184360|last=Baylor|first=Norman W.|last2=Egan|first2=William|date=2002-05-31|journal=Vaccine|doi=10.1016/s0264-410x(02)00166-4|volume=20 Suppl 3|pages=S18–23|issn=0264-410X|pmid=12184360|last3=Richman|first3=Paul|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302034243/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12184360/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Solution to Vaccine Mystery Starts to Crystallize|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/lookup/doi/10.1126/science.341.6141.26|last=Leslie|first=Mitch|date=2013-07-05|journal=Science|issue=6141|doi=10.1126/science.341.6141.26|volume=341|pages=26–27|language=en|issn=0036-8075}}</ref>。有些這類化合物和紅腫、發癢以及輕微的發燒有關聯性<ref name="Baylor" />，不過目前還沒看到在疫苗中用的鋁化合物造成嚴重副作用的例子<ref name="Francois" />。有些案例中，含鋁疫苗與{{le|巨噬細胞肌筋膜炎|macrophagic myofasciitis}}（MMF）有關，這是局部的顯微[[病變|病變]]，在組織中會含有鋁鹽，可能會持續八年的時間，不過最近的病例對照研究發現，在檢體中有巨噬細胞肌筋膜炎的病例中，沒有出現特殊的臨床症狀，也沒有證據顯示含鋁疫苗對健康有重大威脅，或是會造成免疫實務上的變化<ref name="Francois">{{Cite journal|title=Vaccine safety controversies and the future of vaccination programs|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16282928|last=François|first=Guido|last2=Duclos|first2=Philippe|date=2005-11|journal=The Pediatric Infectious Disease Journal|issue=11|doi=10.1097/01.inf.0000183853.16113.a6|volume=24|pages=953–961|issn=0891-3668|pmid=16282928|last3=Margolis|first3=Harold|last4=Lavanchy|first4=Daniel|last5=Siegrist|first5=Claire-Anne|last6=Meheus|first6=André|last7=Lambert|first7=Paul-Henri|last8=Emiroğlu|first8=Nedret|last9=Badur|first9=Selim|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226220625/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16282928/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在嬰兒出生的前六個月中，在日常飲食（如[[母乳|母乳]]及[[嬰兒奶粉|嬰兒奶粉]]）中攝取的鋁多於疫苗中含的鋁<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The problem with Dr Bob's alternative vaccine schedule|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19117838|last=Offit|first=Paul A.|last2=Moser|first2=Charlotte A.|date=2009-01|journal=Pediatrics|issue=1|doi=10.1542/peds.2008-2189|volume=123|pages=e164–169|issn=1098-4275|pmid=19117838|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225220034/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19117838/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Vaccine Ingredients - Aluminum|url=https://www.chop.edu/centers-programs/vaccine-education-center/vaccine-ingredients/aluminum|accessdate=2020-12-20|date=2014-11-04|last=Philadelphia|first=The Children's Hospital of|work=www.chop.edu|language=en|archive-date=2014-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006155039/http://www.chop.edu/service/vaccine-education-center/vaccine-safety/vaccine-ingredients/aluminum.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一般而言，人們經由食物和飲食中就會攝取到很低劑量的鋁<ref name="OxfordVaccineIngredients">{{Cite web |url=http://vk.ovg.ox.ac.uk/vaccine-ingredients#aluminium |title=Vaccine Ingredients |website=Vaccine Knowledge Project |publisher=Centre for Clinical Vaccinology and Tropical Medicine, Churchill Hospital, University of Oxford |access-date=2022-01-07 |archive-date=2021-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210718164344/http://vk.ovg.ox.ac.uk/vaccine-ingredients#aluminium |dead-url=no }}</ref>，疫苗中含的鋁很少，小於1mg，一般認為這麼低的劑量不會對人體有害<ref name="OxfordVaccineIngredients" />。

疫苗猶豫人士也有提到對於疫苗中的[[甲醛|甲醛]]有高度的疑慮。疫苗中的甲醛濃度很低，目的是使疫苗中的病毒和細菌毒素失去活性<ref name="FDAVaccineIngredient" />。疫苗中會殘留非常少量的甲醛，其劑量還不會對人體有害<ref name="CHOPformaldehyde">{{Cite web |url=https://www.chop.edu/centers-programs/vaccine-education-center/vaccine-ingredients/formaldehyde |title=Vaccine Ingredients-Formaldehyde |date=November 6, 2014 |website=chop.edu/ |publisher=Children's Hospital of Philadelphia |access-date=2022-01-09 |archive-date=2021-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019183618/https://www.chop.edu/centers-programs/vaccine-education-center/vaccine-ingredients/formaldehyde |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Vaccineingredients">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vaccines.gov/basics/vaccine_ingredients |title=Vaccine Ingredients |website=vaccines.gov/ |date=April 26, 2021 |publisher=U.S. Department of Health and Human Services |access-date=2022-01-09 |archive-date=2021-04-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210424014807/https://www.vaccines.gov/basics/vaccine_ingredients |dead-url=no }}</ref>。人體中自身就會生成甲醛，疫苗中的甲醛相較於人體原有的甲醛，其劑量微不足道，沒有明顯的毒性風險<ref name="FDAVaccineIngredient">{{Cite web |url=https://www.fda.gov/vaccines-blood-biologics/safety-availability-biologics/common-ingredients-us-licensed-vaccines |title=Common Ingredients Used in U.S. Licensed Vaccines |date=April 19, 2019 |website=fda.gov |publisher=U.S. Food and Drug Administration |access-date=2022-01-09 |archive-date=2021-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020210842/https://www.fda.gov/vaccines-blood-biologics/safety-availability-biologics/common-ingredients-us-licensed-vaccines |dead-url=no }}</ref>。人體自然產生的甲醛，約是疫苗中最大量甲醛的50至70倍<ref name="FDAVaccineIngredient" />。而且，人體可以分解自然產生的甲醛，也可以分解劑量更少，疫苗中的甲醛<ref name="FDAVaccineIngredient" />。目前還沒有證據可以證實疫苗少量甲醛和[[癌症|癌症]]之間的關係<ref name="FDAVaccineIngredient" />。

=== 嬰兒猝死症 ===
[[嬰兒猝死症|嬰兒猝死症]]（SIDS）是嬰兒在接種疫苗的年齡時，很常見的死因<ref name="PediatricsSIDS2016">{{cite journal |last1=Moon |first1=RY |last2=Task Force on Sudden Infant Death Syndrome |title=SIDS and Other Sleep-Related Infant Deaths: Evidence Base for 2016 Updated Recommendations for a Safe Infant Sleeping Environment. |journal=Pediatrics |date=November 2016 |volume=138 |issue=5 |pages=e20162940 |doi=10.1542/peds.2016-2940 |pmid=27940805 |url=https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/138/5/e20162940.long |doi-access=free |access-date=2022-01-09 |archive-date=2021-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210717141004/https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/138/5/e20162940.long |dead-url=no }}</ref>。因為目前還無法完全確定嬰兒猝死症的病因，也有人提出可能是疫苗造成嬰兒猝死症的疑慮，他們認為尤其是白喉-破傷風類毒素疫苗，是可能的致病因素<ref name="PediatricsSIDS2016"/>。目前有幾個研究是以此為主題，目前還找不到證據可以支持疫苗和嬰兒猝死症有因果關係<ref name="PediatricsSIDS2016"/><ref name="2016TaskForceSIDSRecs">{{cite journal |last1=Task Force on Sudden Infant Death Syndrome |title=SIDS and Other Sleep-Related Infant Deaths: Updated 2016 Recommendations for a Safe Infant Sleeping Environment. |journal=Pediatrics |date=November 2016 |volume=138 |issue=5 |pages=e20162938 |doi=10.1542/peds.2016-2938 |pmid=27940804 |url=https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/138/5/e20162938.long |access-date=13 December 2019 |doi-access=free |archive-date=2021-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210719175016/https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/138/5/e20162938.long |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2003年時[[美国国家医学院|美国国家医学院]]審視了已有的證據後，反對將[[百白破疫苗|百白破疫苗]]和SIDS之間加上因果關係<ref>{{cite book |last1=Institute of Medicine (US) Immunization Safety Review Committee |last2=Stratton |first2=K |last3=Almario |first3=DA |last4=Wizemann |first4=TM |last5=McCormick |first5=MC |title=Immunization Safety Review: Vaccinations and Sudden Unexpected Death in Infancy |date=2003 |publisher=National Academies Press (US) |location=Washington D.C. |pmid=25057654 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK221466/pdf/Bookshelf_NBK221466.pdf |access-date=13 December 2019 |archive-date=2020-04-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200412233511/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK221466/pdf/Bookshelf_NBK221466.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另外有關{{link-en|VAERS|VAERS}}資料的分析也找不到疫苗和SIDS之間的因果關系<ref name="PediatricsSIDS2016"/>，研究者發現SID比例和疫苗注射比例上有負相關。有接種疫苗的兒童比較不會有SIDS的症狀。其中一個原因是因為比較不會罹患SIDS的兒童中，多半已注射過流感疫苗<ref name="PediatricsSIDS2016"/><ref name="2016TaskForceSIDSRecs"/><ref name="Vennemann2007">{{cite journal |last1=Vennemann |first1=MM |last2=Höffgen |first2=M |last3=Bajanowski |first3=T |last4=Hense |first4=HW |last5=Mitchell |first5=EA |title=Do immunisations reduce the risk for SIDS? A meta-analysis. |journal=Vaccine |date=June 2007 |volume=25 |issue=26 |pages=4875–79 |doi=10.1016/j.vaccine.2007.02.077 |pmid=17400342}}</ref>。

=== 炭疽疫苗===
1990年代中期有疫苗相關的媒體提到{{link-en|海灣戰爭綜合症|Gulf War Syndrome}}，這是參加過[[海湾战争|海湾战争]]的美國軍人所罹患的多症狀疾病。在線上雜誌《[[Slate|Slate]]》最早出現的報導中，有一篇由是[[阿图·葛文德|阿图·葛文德]]所寫，其中提到軍人要求接種的疫苗，包括{{link-en|炭疽疫苗|Anthrax vaccines}}，是讓軍人得到海灣戰爭綜合症的可能原因之一。《Slate》在1990年代末期發表了軍隊「醞釀叛亂」的文章，軍隊反對接種炭疽疫苗，原因是「士兵很容易接收到網路上有關疫苗的錯誤資訊。」。《Slate》雜誌後來也有報導美國軍人在[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]後強制接種炭疽疫苗和[[天花|天花]]疫苗的疑慮，這些文章也有出現在[[Salon.com|Salon.com]]網站中<ref name="hausman">{{Cite book |title=Anti/Vax: Reframing the Vaccination Controversy |last1=Hausman |first1=Bernice L. |publisher=Cornell University Press |year=2019 |isbn=9781501735639 |pages=28, 39–42}}</ref>。[[2001年美國炭疽攻擊事件|2001年美國炭疽攻擊事件]]加強了對[[生物恐怖主義|生物恐怖主義]]的疑慮，[[美國聯邦政府|美國聯邦政府]]加緊努力為美國公民生產並且保持更多的疫苗<ref name=hausman/>。《[[琼斯母亲|琼斯母亲]]》雜誌在2002年發表了文章，其中強烈懷疑[[美军|美军]]強制接種的炭疽疫苗和天花疫苗<ref name=hausman/>。在{{link-en|2003年美軍入侵伊拉克|2003 invasion of Iraq}}時，因於強制美軍接種炭疽疫苗，在媒體上引發更大一波的爭議<ref name=hausman/>。在2003年至2008年之間，有許多的訴訟案都是為了反對美軍強制接種疫苗<ref name=hausman/>。

=== 流感疫苗 ===
[[File:President_Ford_receives_a_swine_flu_inoculation_-_NARA_-_7064718.jpg|thumb]]接種流感疫苗]]

因應{{link-en|1976年豬流感爆發|1976 swine flu outbreak}}，美國推出了[[豬流感|豬流感]]疫苗計劃，美國總統福特擔心豬流感爆發會造成[[瘟疫|大流行]]，但後來沒有發生，反而是因為匆忙推出的疫苗，在接種後二週造成許多人罹患[[格林－巴利综合征|格林－巴利综合征]]。大眾對[[疫苗接種|疫苗接種]]的恐懼反而病毒本身更大，疫苗接種政策也因此受到挑戰<ref>{{cite book |first=Archana |last=Chatterjee |title=Vaccinophobia and Vaccine Controversies of the 21st Century |publisher=Springer Science & Business Media |year=2013 |pages=8 |isbn=9781461474388}}</ref>。

[[2009年H1N1流感大流行|2009年H1N1流感大流行]]時，法國及其他國家質疑{{le|2009年H1N1流感疫苗|2009 flu pandemic vaccine}}的安全性，許多法國團體批評[[流感疫苗|流感疫苗]]，認為有潛在的危險性<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Rethinking the antivaccine movement concept: A case study of public criticism of the swine flu vaccine's safety in France|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27173740|last=Ward|first=Jeremy K.|date=06 2016|journal=Social Science & Medicine (1982)|doi=10.1016/j.socscimed.2016.05.003|volume=159|pages=48–57|issn=1873-5347|pmid=27173740|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2021-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210810075646/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27173740/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由於2009年A型流感病毒H1N1亞型和1976年流感A/NJ病毒很相似，許多國家建置了有關疫苗相關不良反應對人體影響的監控系統。歐洲和美國也在研究2009 H1N1流感疫苗和格林－巴利综合征之間是否有相關性<ref>{{cite book |first=Archana |last=Chatterjee |title=Vaccinophobia and Vaccine Controversies of the 21st Century |publisher=Springer Science & Business Media |year=2013 |pages=325 |isbn=9781461474388}}</ref>。

=== 其他安全問題 ===
其他有關疫苗安全問題的論點也也常在網路、非正式會議、書籍報章或是研討會上提出。這些假說包括疫苗會造成[[嬰兒猝死症|嬰兒猝死症]]、[[癫痫发作|癫痫发作]]、[[过敏|过敏]]、[[多发性硬化症|多发性硬化症]]以及像[[1型糖尿病|1型糖尿病]]之類的[[自體免疫性疾病|自體免疫性疾病]]等疾病，也有假[[牛腦海綿狀病變|牛腦海綿狀病變]]、[[C型肝炎|C型肝炎]]及[[人類免疫缺陷病毒|人類免疫缺陷病毒]]。研究者已針對這些假說進行確認，結論是目前使用的疫苗符合很高的安全標準，大眾媒體對疫苗安全性的批評並不合理<ref name="Schneeweiss">{{Cite journal|title=Vaccination Safety Update|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2680557/|last=Schneeweiss|first=Burkhard|last2=Pfleiderer|first2=Michael|date=2008-8|journal=Deutsches Ärzteblatt International|issue=34-35|doi=10.3238/arztebl.2008.0590|volume=105|pages=590–595|issn=1866-0452|pmc=2680557|pmid=19471677|last3=Keller-Stanislawski|first3=Brigitte|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2017-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170603224023/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2680557/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。已針對這些假說進行大型且經過良好控制的流行病學研究，結論無法支持疫苗會造成慢性疫病的假說，而且有些疫苗對自體免疫疾病有預防效果的可能性，高於疫苗會造成自體免疫疾病的可能性<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Addressing Parents’ Concerns: Do Vaccines Cause Allergic or Autoimmune Diseases?|url=https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/111/3/653|last=Offit|first=Paul A.|last2=Hackett|first2=Charles J.|date=2003-03-01|journal=Pediatrics|issue=3|doi=10.1542/peds.111.3.653|volume=111|pages=653–659|language=en|issn=0031-4005|pmid=12612250|access-date=2020-12-20|archive-date=2019-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810082801/https://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/111/3/653|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==歷史==
=== 人痘接種術 ===
早期預防[[天花|天花]]的方法包括刻意[[疫苗接種|接種]]人痘的病毒，希望透過較溫和的結果，達致免疫。此方法後來稱為[[人痘接種術|人痘接種術]]，避免和後來[[愛德華·詹納|愛德華·詹納]]發明，接種[[牛痘|牛痘]]（[[疫苗接種|疫苗接種]]）的方式混淆。人痘接種術在中國及印度的歷史長久，北美及英國在1721年才開始在使用該技術。1721年，[[科頓·馬瑟|科頓·馬瑟]]牧師在天花大流行時，在波士頓開始使用人痘接種術<ref name="VaccineControversy">{{cite book|last=Allen|first=Arthur|title=Vaccine: The Controversial Story of Medicine's Greatest Lifesaver|url=https://archive.org/details/vaccinecontrover00arth|year=2007|publisher=W. W. Norton & Company, Inc.|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-393-05911-3|pages=[https://archive.org/details/vaccinecontrover00arth/page/25 25]–36}}</ref>。當時，許多人以宗教的理由反對，但马瑟牧師相信[[扎布迪尔·博伊尔斯顿|扎布迪尔·博伊尔斯顿]]醫師，繼續嘗試。博伊爾斯頓一開始在他六歲的孩子、奴隶及奴隶的儿子試驗，三人都發病數天，然後病症就消失了<!-- is "miraculously vanished" a direct quote? -->，之後就「不再重病缠身」<ref name="VaccineControversy" />。博伊爾斯頓後來為上千個马萨诸塞州的居民接種人痘，許多地方都因為感激他，以他作為地方的名稱。{{le|玛丽·蒙塔古·沃特利夫人|Lady Mary Wortley Montagu}}將人痘接種術引進英國。她自己已經在土耳其看過，而且1718年在{{le|查尔斯·梅特兰|Charles Maitland (physician)}}医生的監督下，她讓她的兒子成功的在君士坦丁堡接種了人痘。她在1721年回到了英國，她讓梅特兰醫師為她的女兒接種人痘。這引起了大眾的注意力，[[汉斯·斯隆|汉斯·斯隆]]爵士在{{le|紐蓋特監獄|Newgate Prison}}為一些犯人接種人痘。這幾次都很成功，而在1722年的另一次試驗後，威爾斯公主[[卡羅琳_(安斯巴赫)|卡羅琳]]的二個女兒也接種了人痘，沒有發生意外。在王室批准後，當天花疫情加劇時，接種人痘也就更加常見了<ref name="williams">{{cite book|last=Williams|first=Gareth|title=Angel Of Death; the story of smallpox|url=https://archive.org/details/angeldeathstorys00will|year=2010|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|location=Basingstoke, UK|isbn=978 0 230 27471 6|pages=[https://archive.org/details/angeldeathstorys00will/page/87 87]–94}}</ref>。

很快就出現了{{le|疫苗和宗教|Vaccination and religion|宗教上反對接種疫苗}}的意見。例如在1772年英文神学家牧师埃德蒙·梅西（Edmund Massey）在一篇名為「接種疫苗是危險及有罪的行為」的講道中，他提到疾病是神用來懲罰罪人的工具，因此任何想要藉由接種疫苗預防天花的方法是「惡魔的作為」<ref name="Early">早期宗教上對疫苗接種的反對：

* {{cite book|chapter=Theological opposition to inoculation, vaccination, and the use of anæsthetics|title=A History of the Warfare of Science with Theology in Christendom|author=White AD|location=New York|publisher=Appleton|year=1896|chapterurl=http://abob.libs.uga.edu/bobk/whitem10.html|access-date=2016-09-13|archive-date=2008-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080917184044/http://abob.libs.uga.edu/bobk/whitem10.html|dead-url=no}}
* {{Cite journal|title=The ethics of vaccine usage in society: lessons from the past|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11725304|last=Bazin|first=H.|date=2001-09|journal=Endeavour|issue=3|doi=10.1016/s0160-9327(00)01376-4|volume=25|pages=104–108|issn=0160-9327|pmid=11725304|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221214708/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/11725304/|dead-url=no}}
* {{Cite journal|title=Ethics in the trenches: a multifaceted analysis of the stem cell debate|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17142878|last=Noble|first=Mark|date=2005-12|journal=Stem Cell Reviews|issue=4|doi=10.1385/SCR:1:4:345|volume=1|pages=345–376|issn=1558-6804|pmid=17142878|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221214519/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17142878/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當時著名的牧師常會發表其講章，有許多的受眾。像梅西的講章就影響了北美，北美也是早期反對接種疫苗的地方，而當時的[[约翰·威廉姆斯|约翰·威廉姆斯]]牧師也反對。另一個反對疫苗的意見是來自住在波士頓的[[威廉·道格拉斯|威廉·道格拉斯]]醫生，他是[[爱丁堡大学|爱丁堡大学]]的醫學畢業生，也是{{le|英國皇家學會成員|Fellow of the Royal Society}}<ref name="williams" />{{rp|114–22}}。

=== 牛痘接種術 ===
[[愛德華·詹納|愛德華·詹納]]在1798年發明[[牛痘接種術|牛痘接種術]]來預防天花之後，人痘接種術開始絕跡，在一些國家更被禁止採用<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A brief history of the prevention of infectious diseases by immunisations|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12818618/|last=Bazin|first=Hervé|date=2003-10|journal=Comparative Immunology, Microbiology and Infectious Diseases|issue=5-6|doi=10.1016/S0147-9571(03)00016-X|volume=26|pages=293–308|issn=0147-9571|pmid=12818618|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2021-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210810075518/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12818618/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Smallpox: gone but not forgotten|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9795781/|last=Ellner|first=P. D.|date=1998-09|journal=Infection|issue=5|doi=10.1007/BF02962244|volume=26|pages=263–269|issn=0300-8126|pmid=9795781|access-date=2020-12-19|archive-date=2022-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220112160624/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9795781/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
[[File:Edward_Jenner2.jpg|thumb]]

和人痘接種術的情形類似，基督教人士中有反對使用牛痘接種術的意見，但有牧師（如罗伯特·费里曼牧師和[[罗兰·希尔|罗兰·希尔]]）在講道中支持牛痘接種術，也親自去接種牛痘<ref name="williams" />{{rp|221}}。也有人痘接種者因龐大利益無法獨佔而反對牛痘接種。威廉·罗利發表聲稱是因為接種疫苗而導致畸形的插图，在同一頁有[[詹姆斯·吉爾雷|詹姆斯·吉爾雷]]著名的嘲諷漫畫。本杰明·莫斯利將牛痘連結到[[梅毒|梅毒]]，這個爭議一直持續到20世紀<ref name="williams" />{{rp|203–5}}。

疫苗支持者由於疫苗安全有效，希望議院加以重視，但是當議院開始要強制注射疫苗時，卻受到社會大眾的普遍譴責。其原因是因為疫苗導入時，當時還沒有對應的實驗方法可以控管其製造過程，也無法找到疫苗失效的原因<ref name="baxby2001">{{cite book|last=Baxby|first=Derrick|title=Smallpox Vaccine, Ahead of its Time|year=2001|publisher=the Jenner Museum|location=Berkeley, UK|isbn=0 9528695 1 9|pages=12–21}}</ref>。疫苗最早是透過手臂和手臂接觸的方式轉換，後來是利用動物的皮膚製造，不可能作到無菌的消毒。而且一直到19世紀末到20世紀初才有識別潛在病源體的方法。之後發現有些病症是因為疫苗受到病源體污染而造成，造成的病症有[[丹毒|丹毒]]、[[結核|結核]]、[[破傷風|破傷風]]及梅毒。後者的機率很很低，約一億個人中才有750個病例<ref name="bazin2000">{{cite book|last=Bazin|first=Hervé|title=The Eradication of Smallpox|url=https://archive.org/details/eradicationofsma0000bazi|year=2000|publisher=Academic Press|location=London|isbn=0 12 083475 8|page=[https://archive.org/details/eradicationofsma0000bazi/page/122 122]}}</ref>，但格外的受到重視。很多以後，醫界反對接種疫苗的領導人物{{le|查尔斯·克赖顿|Charles Creighton}}醫生，認為疫苗本身就是造成梅毒的原因，而且為了此議題寫了一本書<ref name="creighton">{{cite book|last=Creighton|first=Charles|title=The Natural History of Cowpox and Vaccinal Syphilis|year=1887|publisher=Cassell|location=London}}</ref>。後來有些已接種過牛痘疫苗的人再度出現牛痘症狀，疫苗支持者指出這些人的症狀相當輕微，而且是在接種疫苗後幾年才出現症狀。但反對者就認為這和詹納認為接種疫苗就完全免疫的說法矛盾<ref name=baxby2001/>{{rp|17–21}}。疫苗反對者認為疫苗既危險又無效，因此當英國議院開始要強制接種疫苗時，英國各地發起了反疫苗活動<ref name="williamson">{{cite book|last=Williamson|first=Stanley|title=The Vaccination Controversy; the rise, reign and decline of compulsory vaccination|year=2007|publisher=Liverpool University Press|location=Liverpool|isbn=9781846310867}}</ref>。
